PART A: PROJECT OVERVIEW 
1. PROJECT IDEA DEFINITION

Retail watch shops handle many transactions daily involving customers purchasing watches of different brands, models, and materials. In many small retail businesses, sales records and inventory tracking are still done manually using notebooks or spreadsheets. This method often leads to data redundancy, inaccurate inventory records, lost transaction details, and difficulty tracking customer purchases or supplier information.

The proposed system is a Watch Retail Shop Database System designed to store and manage information related to watches, suppliers, customers, employees, orders, payments, and warranties. The database will allow the shop to record all sales transactions, track inventory, and manage relationships with customers and suppliers.

By implementing this system, the shop will improve efficiency, reduce data redundancy, maintain accurate sales records, and generate useful reports for business management.

2. SCOPE AND OBJECTIVES
SCOPE

The scope of the system focuses on managing the main operations of a watch retail shop. The database will manage information about:

Watches sold in the shop

Suppliers who provide watches

Customers purchasing watches

Employees processing orders

Orders placed by customers

Payments for purchases

Warranties issued for watches

The system mainly supports sales processing and record management.

OBJECTIVES

The objectives of the system are:

To design a structured database for storing watch shop information.

To record and track customer orders.

To maintain information about suppliers and watches supplied.

To store payment details for each transaction.

To track warranties issued for watches.

To improve efficiency and reduce manual record keeping.

3.STAKEHOLDERS
Shop Owner

The owner uses the system to monitor sales performance, inventory levels, and customer activity.

Employees

Employees interact with the system when recording orders, processing sales, and managing customer information.

Customers

Customers benefit indirectly as the system ensures accurate order processing and proper warranty tracking.

Suppliers

Suppliers provide watches to the shop, and their details are stored in the system.

System Administrator

The administrator manages the database system and ensures its proper operation.
